This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with object localization and motion prediction in images. It also involves machine learning techniques such as CapsNet and LSTM networks, which are commonly used in computer vision research. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories due to the use of deep learning models and transfer learning techniques. The robotics (cs.RO) category is also a possibility as the paper deals with object motion prediction, which is relevant to robotics applications. Finally, the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category may also be relevant as CapsNet is a neural network architecture.
